# Phase 3.1 — Hot-reload SDK for resource development.
#
# This one needs NO C++ patch — it's a pure JS/Lua resource that wraps CFX's
# existing `restart <name>` console command with a file-watcher.
#
# Lives as a standalone resource (not in alfamp-client patches/):
#   compat-rage/resources/alfa-hotreload/
#
# When a dev saves any .lua/.js/.cs/.fxmanifest file inside a watched resource,
# the resource is auto-restarted. Players stay connected; only that resource
# blinks (CFX preserves player session across resource restarts).
#
# Behavior:
#   - Only active when convar `sv_devMode` is true (prod servers ignore).
#   - Debounced 500 ms so save-spam doesn't restart 10× per second.
#   - Reports to admin console: "[hotreload] resource X restarted (3 files changed)".
#
# Implementation is in: compat-rage/resources/alfa-hotreload/server.lua
# (a small 60-line Lua resource — no patch needed).
